    works to carry a different name or version number from the original software;
5. The license must not discriminate against any person or group of persons;
6. The license must not restrict anyone from making use of the program in a specific field of
  endeavour;
7. The rights attached to the program must apply to all to whom the program is redistributed,
  without the need for execution of an additional license by those parties;
8. The rights attached to the program must not depend on the program being part of a particular
  software distribution;
9. The license must not place restrictions on other software that is distributed along with the licensed
  software; and
10. No provision of the license may be predicated on any individual technology or style of interface.


